# FEATURES.md is administrative state owned by the dispatcher.
# Feature branches (Ralph worktrees) often mark rows `done` on their side,
# which conflicts with main's concurrent row edits when multiple dispatches
# run in parallel. Declaring merge=ours makes main's version always win on
# merge, so branches stay mergeable without manual conflict resolution.
# The dispatcher updates FEATURES.md directly on main post-merge.
#
# Required local config (one-time, per checkout):
#   git config merge.ours.driver true
context/FEATURES.md merge=ours
